reviews.review_text: Great Sounding Aud I don't know why no one has taken the time to review this hidden jem. I'm thinking it's because it is an old audience recording. The sound quality is very good on this. I like this better than the Dick's Pick. There is a perfect balance with the crowd and the music. And the music...Typical 1977. I highly recomend this show. Again, it sounds incredible.

My First Show It's good to see that this show is available again after it was release as part if the Dick's Picks series. A solid start in a lifetime of shows where I lost count after 100 (no including Jerry, Bobby, Phil, Mickey and their assorted incarnations then & now). Except for the sound drop off on the second track, a solid quality show. As an ex-taper, I've always enjoyed the rawness of an audience tape. Sentimentality may creep into it, but I say this is a definite download!
Eyes This recording allows you to hear Phil's playing clearly. Listen to the Eyes, it's so sweet! Great sound quality!

A gem We all like sbds, but good audience recordings are valuable for two reasons.  One, it is good to hear the ambiance of the band's sound.  Two, you get a real sense of the "spirit" in the house.  This is an outstanding quality aud. and well worth the listen.
